reviews.review: Great end to the saga! It tied everything together nicely.

Star Wars the original saga is about a family thats why this movie is great also its great because its great I worry that a lot of fans expect every little thing they ever really wanted ever out of everything ever We got a calm down and realize the original stories about the family

I loved it gets in my top 4 all time star was movies it was emotional roller coaster so much more than End game was for me. Great last movie staying very true to the original 3 movies as I felt left little bit underwhelmed with the most recent movies.. but this movie another excellent job by J.J Abraham's he just makes brilliant scifi movies.
All the critics are Scrooge’s. It’s not perfect, but is the best of the new trilogy.
Great Movie!! Fantastic way to end it.

I think this movie did the best job possible to fix all the messes set up my episode 8. There is some pacing issues and some plot points that get glossed over, but that is largely due to the fact that they had to do so much “apologizing” for the last movie. I’m very satisfied with how the trilogy ended and wish JJ would have had control of all 3 movies.

I heard so many bad things about this movie. I assumed I would hate it, like I hated The Last Jedi. JJ Abrams spends the first half trying to undo the disaster of the last movie and course correct leading to a few times where I laughed at how ludicrous the plot was. The Force Awakens copied the originals too closely. The Last Jedi disprected them. But this one built on them. Overall I enjoyed it and am quite satisfied. The best of this newest trilogy.

Rise of Skywalker brings it all together, as a Star Wars fan my whole life the references to all the other movies and hat tipping to tons of great characters made me very happy. A little campy sure but let’s face it JJ saved the debacle Johnson left him and another hat tip to the shots JJ took at the terrible decisions Johnson made. Simply put I Loved it and all Star Wars real fans should as well, as a movie on its own it’s action packed and has some great moments.

Amazing movie and great finish to 9 films. There is no way possible to perfectly end a huge saga but this was the best possible attempt. Only wish jj had done episode 8 and was able to flesh out some of these new ideas on that movie instead.
JJ Abrams has truly nailed it with this movie. Engaging, fast-paced, and visually spectacular, he has given the timeless Star Wars saga the truly epic conclusion it deserves.
